verbs.description: untune (third-person singular simple present untunes, present participle untuning, simple past and past participle untuned)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To cause (something) to be out of tune; to make incapable of harmony, or of harmonious action.
examples: […]  do we not see in most collections that much time disunites, untunes, blackens, and by degrees destroys even the best preserved pictures.
